Health Practitioners Tribunal (Fees) Regulations 2020

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, make the following regulations under the Health Practitioners Tribunal Act 2010 .

16 November 2020

C. WARNER

Governor

By Her Excellency's Command,

ELISE ARCHER

Minister for Justice

1. Short title
    These regulations may be cited as the Health Practitioners Tribunal (Fees) Regulations 2020 .

2. Commencement
    These regulations take effect on the day on which their making is notified in the Gazette.

3. Fee
    For the purposes of section 21(6)(e) of the Health Practitioners Tribunal Act 2010 , the prescribed fee for an application under section 21(2) or (4) of that Act is 150 fee units.

4. Legislation rescinded
    The legislation specified in Schedule 1 is rescinded.

SCHEDULE 1 - Legislation rescinded

Regulation 4

Health Practitioners Tribunal (Fees) Regulations 2010 (No. 79 of 2010)
                                                                      


Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 25 November 2020

These regulations are administered in the Department of Justice.
